Police have arrested the owner of a face-mask factory in Umhlanga, Durban after his employees were locked up for several days on the premises, working without any payment. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Police have arrested the owner of a face-mask factory in Umhlanga, Durban. The owner allegedly locked up his employees for several days on the premises, forcing them to work without any payment. KZN Economic Development MEC Nomusa Dube Ncube expressed shock over the incident. SA Lockdown: Army deployment is money well spent - expert "We are working together wit the police as well as the department of labour and the workers ave already been taken back to their homes and the police have taken custody of the owner", she said. The MEC also condemned the factory security guards who tried to stop the department officials from gaining access into the factory following the owners arrest.